column5: was thinking of exploring sen bay this spring, is sen a good spring spot for eyes??? any help would be great. 6 weeks to the opener, hey

Fished it for 27yr late June and Sept. We hit it one day in our week of fishing. E -mail me if you like. Tell me when and where else you fish Lac Suel I'll send you our hot spots. ( Look me up in profiles)
We fish there in August. It is great. Hardly another boat, most just pass on through. You should be able to find a lot of fish. Good luck.
We've found it to be more of a summer spot so we have not done much there. We did try up into Archer lake thinking that it was going to be a shallow warm bay but did not do well.
